    "title": "Epoxy Floors for Healthcare Facilities - Elite South Texas",
    "content": "Healthcare\nThe healthcare industry requires flooring engineered for heavy traffic from portable medical equipment, etc. These specialty seamless flooring systems are non-porous providing an antimicrobial surface. The surface is also resistant to chemical and biological fluids and withstands frequent aggressive cleaning.\nAdvantages\nAntimicrobial and stain resistant\nSeamless, non-porous surfaces\nEasy to clean and maintain\nChemical resistant and engineered to withstand aggressive cleaning\nUltra-durable, high abrasion resistance withstands heavy traffic and equipment\nFluid applied systems for new construction or existing floor restoration\nFinish options include gloss or satin\nVariable coefficient of friction (COF) levels to meet or exceed ADA Flat Surfaces, ADA Inclined Surfaces, OSHA and NFPA requirements\nSPECIFICATION OVERVIEW\u200b\nTYPICAL AREAS OF USE\u200b\nLobby and public areas\nOffices\nPatient rooms\nLaboratory and testing facilities\nDiagnosis rooms\nOperating rooms\nPharmacies\nEmergency rooms\nX-ray and MRI facilities\nKitchens and cafeterias\nRestrooms and locker rooms\nMechanical and custodial areas\nOther Resources\nChemical Resistance Chart\nParamount\nUrethane Cement",
